<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}-{5}{y}={24}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{x}+{4}{y}=-{12}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({4},-{4}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}+-{5}{y}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}={24}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{24}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{1}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{\left(\frac{{{24}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{1}}\right)}+{4}{y}=-{12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{1}}{{1}}\cdot{\left({24}\right)}-\frac{{1}}{{1}}{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}+{4}{y}=-{12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{24}-{\left({5}\right)}{y}+{4}{y}=-{12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{y}+{\left({4}\right)}{y}=-{12}-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{y}+{\left({4}\right)}{y}=-{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({5}+{\left({4}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{y}=-{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{36}}{{9}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{4}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}+-{5}{\left(-{4}\right)}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}+{\left({20}\right)}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}={24}-{\left({20}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}={4}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{4}}{{1}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({4},-{4}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>